Kashim Shettima, vice-presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), met with Godswill Akpabio, former minister of Niger Delta Affairs, on Saturday. Shetima was accompanied by Ali Ndume, the senator representing Borno south. The former Borno state governor also visited Rochas Okorocha, senator representing Imo west. Okorocha was one of the contenders in the APC presidential primary which was won by Bola Tinubu, the standard bearer of the party. Here are pictures from both visits.        